Rating: 0
For those who don't think this soup has enough flavor, saute fresh garlic, fresh fennel, onion and celery in butter til soft. Add turnip and sweat further. Then add chicken stock and simmer til turnips are done. Puree and add cream. sometimes I stir in crumbled crisp bacon right before serving.

Rating: 3
I only had about a half pound of turnips so I made up the difference with an assortment of potatoes from my CSA box, subbed the butter for olive oil and the milk for almond milk, making it dairy-free and it was delicious! Oh, and I didn't have the tops so I sautéed kale with garlic and garnished with that.

Rating: 4
A lovely, sustaining fall soup. Beautiful little white turnips from the farmers market didn't need to be peeled or pre-boiled, and the greens were very tender. A stick blender made it so easy. Everyone loved it--kids too. A keeper.

