this really lacked flavor, the thyme was actually quite nice, but it wasn't enough for us.

Rating: 3
This was, much to my surprise, pretty good. I didn't have 4 cups of milk, so I used 2 cups whole milk, 1 cup 2% milk, 1/2 cup heavy cream, and 1/2 cup water. The soup turned out rich yet light. The fresh thyme is necessary - I can't imagine how flavorless this would be if you tried to use dried. The sauteed greens on top absolutely make the soup. Don't skip that part! Oh, and it only took me about 10 minutes to cook the soup until the turnips were tender.